---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro'
const lastUpdated = '2026-06-10'
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Pilot.BM privacy policy. Privacy-first by default: no analytics, no tracking cookies. Third-party map embeds load only on your request."
>
  <section style="background-color: var(--color-sand); padding-block: var(--space-10);">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 style="font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: var(--text-3xl);">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p style="color: var(--color-muted); font-size: var(--text-sm);">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="container" style="padding-block: var(--space-12);">
    <div style="max-width: 720px;" class="prose">

      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>
        Pilot.BM is built with privacy as a default, not an afterthought.
        This page explains what data we collect and how we use it.
      </p>

      <h2>Analytics</h2>
      <p>
        Pilot.BM does <strong>not currently run any analytics</strong> — no page-view tracking, no
        personal data collection, no fingerprinting. If we add a privacy-first, cookieless analytics
        tool (such as Plausible) in future, we will update this page before turning it on.
      </p>

      <h2>No tracking cookies</h2>
      <p>
        Pilot.BM does not place tracking cookies. We do not use Google Analytics, Facebook Pixel,
        or any other third-party tracking cookies on our pages.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-party embeds</h2>
      <p>
        A small number of pages display content from third parties. We keep this minimal and, where a
        third party may set storage on your device, we load it only when you choose to:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>NOAA / National Hurricane Center outlook graphics</strong> (on the Hurricane Season
          page) are public-domain U.S. government weather images, hot-linked unaltered. They load
          automatically and carry no tracking.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Ventusky interactive weather map</strong> (on the Hurricane Season page) loads
          <em>only</em> when you click "Load interactive map". Once loaded, Ventusky (ventusky.com) may
          set its own storage per its privacy policy. We store nothing ourselves and remember no consent
          between visits.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Approximate-location lookup</strong> (the "how far are you from Bermuda?" toy on the
          home page) runs <em>only</em> when you tap the button. It sends your IP address to a
          third-party geolocation service (geojs.io, with ipwho.is as a fallback) to estimate your
          city and distance to Bermuda. The result is shown to you only — we do not store it, share it,
          or display it to anyone else.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Web fonts</strong> are served from Google Fonts on every page (no cookies set by the
          font request).
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Affiliate links</h2>
      <p>
        When you click an affiliate link, you are transferred to a third-party site.
        That site may use cookies per its own privacy policy. We have no control over third-party
        cookie practices. Active affiliate networks are listed in our
        <a href="/Pilot.BM/legal/affiliate-disclosure">affiliate disclosure</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Forms</h2>
      <p>
        If you submit the directory claim form, we receive: your business name, email address,
        and tier selection. This data is used only to process your listing claim.
        We do not sell or share this data with third parties.
      </p>

      <h2>Email</h2>
      <p>
        If you contact us by email, we retain your email and the content of the message
        for correspondence purposes. We do not add you to a mailing list without your consent.
      </p>

      <h2>Data retention</h2>
      <p>
        Contact form data and email correspondence: retained for up to 2 years.
        Analytics data (aggregated, no personal data): retained per Plausible's terms.
      </p>

      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights to access, correct, or delete personal data
        we hold about you. To exercise these rights, contact:
        <a href="mailto:matt@ravenpower.net">matt@ravenpower.net</a>
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy. Changes will be reflected in the "Last updated" date above.
        Continued use of the Site after changes constitutes acceptance.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Privacy questions: <a href="mailto:matt@ravenpower.net">matt@ravenpower.net</a>
      </p>

    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
